parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or hesitate while shifting gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates while shifting gears
the transmission jerks or surges
the vehicle makes a loud clicking or knocking noise
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle has difficulty accelerating
the transmission makes a loud whining or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to rattle or make a loud noise, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The engine rattles or makes a loud noise
especially during startup
the timing chain makes a loud clicking or knocking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the linear solenoids can cause problems with vehicle shifting, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle has difficulty shifting gears
the transmission jerks or surges
the vehicle makes a loud clicking or knocking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crank position sensor can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle won't start
the engine stalls while driving
the vehicle has difficulty starting after sitting stationary.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause fires, leading to safety risks and potential damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The lights start flashing
the wipers start going
smoke appears
the vehicle catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag light to flash, leading to concerns about safety and potential risks in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light flashes
the cluster that reads over hearing and miles flashes and twitches.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel can cause the horn, radio, and instrument panel to fail without warning, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The horn
radio
and instrument panel fail without warning
the service engine and airbag warning lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of gas, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The gas gauge shows full but the car stops in the middle of the road
the gas gauge is inaccurate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hatch lift can cause the hatch to not close or open, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The hatch lift will not close or open with the key or push button
the hatch is stuck in an open position.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Odometer and Gas Gauge Display Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the odometer and gas gauge display can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's mileage and fuel level, leading to safety risks and inconvenience.
symptoms: The last three digits of the mileage become garbled
the odometer display fails
the gas gauge display fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic gas pedal assembly can cause the vehicle to shut down while driving, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while driving
no gas pedal response
no power steering
no power brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS and Traction Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and traction control system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Illumination of the ABS
traction control
and slip warning lights on the instrument panel
vibration coming from the front end of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature tire wear can lead to tire failure, causing accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Tires wear out quickly
becoming treadless and showing cord wear
tire sensors may not detect flat tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brake rotors and pads wear out quickly
brake pedals shake when pressed
uneven brake wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to notify customers of necessary brake maintenance can lead to brake system failure, causing accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: No warning or notification of brake pad wear
brake pins not checked during routine maintenance.
